# Gitleaks fingerprint allowlist for accepted findings that a real
# full-history scan (`gitleaks git -c .gitleaks.toml`, see
# .github/workflows/ci.yml) would otherwise flag. This is gitleaks' own
# fingerprint mechanism — one exact commit:file:rule:line per entry — kept
# separate from the broader path/regex allowlist in .gitleaks.toml.
#
# To regenerate an entry: run the scan locally with
# `--report-format json --report-path -`, then copy the finding's
# "Fingerprint" field verbatim. Never hand-type one; a single wrong
# character means it silently stops suppressing anything.
#
# Format: commit:file:rule-id:start-line

